column5: Well GB came out today and we went back to the panfish zone.. not too much happening, would have helped if we had real bait, lol. Eventually we figured out that bread balls worked pretty well for bluegill. Only one keeper perch caught all day but quite a few bluegills to keep us occupied. No pike however.
LOL RICH  I nearly ended up down there myself this morning. Decided to stay in PD. But i am gonna hit that spot early am tommorow. Atleast you caught a fish all i caught was a suntan....lol......
There will be a few of us down there tomorrow, not in your spot dont worry, lol. I guess we'll see ya there.
Better not be my spot or i will take the broom handle to ya again  See ya in the morning.
nice fishing man! those gills sure are fun when nothing else is bitting. we will get into some fish tomorrow

Nice report and pics Rich. Those blue gills really have some nice coulors. Also, I was wondering how do you clean blue gills. Because if we ever get some ice this year, I was thinking of going to Valens for some blue gills. And also, what size range is considered a keeper?

Good luck with the fishing tomorrow...er....today......um......whenever. DANG ! I have to get to bed. Crap, it's 4:30 am Kiddies will be up in a couple of hours.  Post a report with some more pics Rich.  tight lines
